<h3>
 Question 1
</h3>
<co-content>
 <p>
  If you have a classification problem with multiple labels, how does the neural network architecture change?
 </p>
</co-content>
<form>
 <label>
  <input name="0" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    Instead of a logistic layer, use a softmax layer
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="0" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    Have a logistic layer for each label, and send the outputs of the logistic layer to a softmax layer
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
</form>
<hr/>
<h3>
 Question 2
</h3>
<co-content>
 <p>
  If you have thousands of classes, computing the cross-entropy loss can be very slow.  Which of these is a way to help address that problem?
 </p>
</co-content>
<form>
 <label>
  <input name="1" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    Use a noise-contrastive loss function
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
 <label>
  <input name="1" type="radio"/>
  <co-content>
   <span>
    Combine the categories hierarchically and train multi-stage neural networks
   </span>
  </co-content>
  <br/>
 </label>
</form>
<hr/>
